## CSS Bug Report: Chat Popup

### Bug 1: `color-mix()` CSS function â€” unsupported in older browsers

**Files affected:** `packages/ai-tutor/src/components/`
- `ChatWidget.tsx:418-419` â€” error message background
- `ProactiveMessagePreview.tsx:23` â€” high-priority message background
- `NotificationCenter.tsx:185, 252, 270, 280` â€” filter tab active bg, unread row bg, category label bg, priority label bg
- `ContextSuggestionCard.tsx:19` â€” suggestion card background
- `MissingKeyBanner.tsx:11` â€” warning banner background

**Also in:** `apps/web/src/components/aiTutor/FloatingTutorButton.tsx:14-15` â€” pulse animation keyframes

**Detail:** CSS `color-mix(in srgb, ...)` is widely supported only since Chrome 111 (Mar 2023), Firefox 113 (May 2023), Safari 16.2 (Dec 2022). In unsupported browsers, the value is treated as invalid, so the `background-color` falls back to `transparent`. This makes text unreadable against the popup surface (especially `var(--color-on-primary, #fff)` white text on a transparent background).

**Recommendation:** Replace with `rgba()` or `hsla()` equivalents, or use CSS variables with fallback values (e.g., `var(--color-danger-light, rgba(239,68,68,0.08))`).

**Severity:** Medium â€” affects visual rendering in any browser without `color-mix` support.

